{"title":"All-new Canyon Torque freeride bike hits bike parks with tons of slack alloy, carbon & mullet options","link":"https://bikerumor.com/all-new-canyon-torque-freeride-bike-hits-bike-parks-with-tons-of-slack-alloy-carbon-mullet-options/","date":1638814655000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103949/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Sam-Soriano-dropping-in-Utah-desert.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103949/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Sam-Soriano-dropping-in-Utah-desert-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Torque freeride bikepark bike, Samantha Soriano dropping in\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103949/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Sam-Soriano-dropping-in-Utah-desert-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103949/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Sam-Soriano-dropping-in-Utah-desert-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103949/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Sam-Soriano-dropping-in-Utah-desert-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103949/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Sam-Soriano-dropping-in-Utah-desert-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103949/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Sam-Soriano-dropping-in-Utah-desert-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103949/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Sam-Soriano-dropping-in-Utah-desert.jpg 2000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-280083\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Canyon has completely overhauled their Torque freeride bike for a new season of shredding bike parks, EWS tracks &amp; jump lines with tons of options to suit any gravity rider. Pick from full carbon or alloy framesets and 27.5, 29″ or mullet wheel builds to get the perfect setup for your own personal style of gravity riding – whether you’re shuttling, catching a chairlift, or pedaling to the top for each run…</p><h2>2022 Canyon Torque freeride, park bike</h2><div id=\"attachment_280116\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103943/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-riding-Schladming.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-280116\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103943/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-riding-Schladming.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Torque freeride bikepark bike, Schladming airtime\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103943/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-riding-Schladming.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103943/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-riding-Schladming-297x178.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103943/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-riding-Schladming-800x480.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103943/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-riding-Schladming-120x72.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103943/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-riding-Schladming-768x461.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103943/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-riding-Schladming-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-280116\"><em>all photos c. Canyon</em></p></div><p>Canyon says the new Torque was completely redesigned to be their ‘one’ long-travel mountain bike for riders looking to go from all-mountain enduro riding, to week-long trips to bike parks, to full-tilt backcountry freeriding. With&nbsp;slacker headtube angles, longer reach, steeper seattube angles, and more options for wheelsizes, this is the longer version of their popular <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/?s=spectral\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">all-mountain Spectral</a> that can still climb when needed, and is meant to be more versatile than the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019-canyon-strive-shapeshifts-again-into-all-new-v2-0-29er-enduro-bike/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">enduro race-specific Strive</a>.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103940/2022-Canyon-Torque-CF7-freeride-bike_carbon-275-MTB-complete.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103940/2022-Canyon-Torque-CF7-freeride-bike_carbon-275-MTB-complete.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Torque freeride bikepark bike, complete\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1125\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103940/2022-Canyon-Torque-CF7-freeride-bike_carbon-275-MTB-complete.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103940/2022-Canyon-Torque-CF7-freeride-bike_carbon-275-MTB-complete-297x167.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103940/2022-Canyon-Torque-CF7-freeride-bike_carbon-275-MTB-complete-800x450.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103940/2022-Canyon-Torque-CF7-freeride-bike_carbon-275-MTB-complete-120x68.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103940/2022-Canyon-Torque-CF7-freeride-bike_carbon-275-MTB-complete-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103940/2022-Canyon-Torque-CF7-freeride-bike_carbon-275-MTB-complete-1536x864.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p>For riders of the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021-canyon-spectral-29-cf-reshapes-lighter-more-capable-adjustable-do-it-all-carbon-trail-bike/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">recently-overhauled Spectral</a>, this new Canyon Torque looks very familiar – like a bigger, longer travel sibling. Much of the tech, materials, and wheelsize choices are the same, just scaled up for steeper terrain and bigger jumps.</p><p>New Torque buyers can pick from 27.5, Mullet &amp; 29″ wheel setups as Canyon built the new freeride bike around the same modular design concept as the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/review-canyon-spectral-mullet-cf-cllctv-shifts-capable-trail-bike-to-enduro/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">latest Spectral</a> – with unique front &amp; rear triangles for 27.5 or 29″ wheels.</p><p>27.5 bikes get 175mm or rear wheel travel, paired to 180mm forks. 29″ bikes get 170mm of rear wheel travel, paired to 170mm forks.</p><p>So, the mullet bikes get the 170mm rear wheel travel of the 27.5″ rear triangle &amp; rear wheel, combined with the&nbsp;170mm front wheel travel of the 29er front triangle, 29er fork &amp; bigger front wheel.</p><h3>Updated Gravity Geometry</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103936/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-riding-at-bikepark-Schladming.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103936/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-riding-at-bikepark-Schladming.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Torque freeride bikepark bike, Schladming airtime\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103936/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-riding-at-bikepark-Schladming.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103936/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-riding-at-bikepark-Schladming-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103936/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-riding-at-bikepark-Schladming-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103936/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-riding-at-bikepark-Schladming-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103936/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-riding-at-bikepark-Schladming-768x576.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103936/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-riding-at-bikepark-Schladming-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>Although Canyon doesn’t sell the front &amp; rear ends separately, they are essentially a mix &amp; match design concept. The result is that gravity-ready geometry is almost exactly the same no matter which wheelsize combo you pick (outside of 5mm shorter chainstays for the smaller rear wheel).</p><p>The differing ride character of each choice then boils down to the variation in stability/maneuverability of the various wheelsizes, individual wheel stiffness &amp; tire contact patch, and the balance of wheel rollover vs. a little extra travel.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103931/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_adpatable-geometry.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103931/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_adpatable-geometry.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Torque freeride bikepark bike, gravity-ready geometry\" width=\"2000\" height=\"870\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103931/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_adpatable-geometry.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103931/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_adpatable-geometry-297x129.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103931/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_adpatable-geometry-800x348.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103931/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_adpatable-geometry-120x52.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103931/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_adpatable-geometry-768x334.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103931/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_adpatable-geometry-1536x668.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p>The new bikes get almost two degree slacker 63.5° head angles, 2-3.5cm longer reach, and up to four degrees steeper seattube angles. The carbon bikes also now get Canyon’s adjustable <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2022-canyon-spectral-all-mountain-goes-big-in-new-alloy-kids-cfr-mullet-trail-to-enduro-bikes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">flip-chip</a> at the lower shock mount that lets riders pick Hi or Lo settings that shift the head &amp; seat angles by 0.5° and shift BB height by 8mm.</p><p>Alloy bikes don’t get the flip-chip, instead combining a ‘best of both worlds’ slack 63.5° head angle and Lo BB with the steeper 78° HI seat angle.</p><p>The new Canyon Torque comes in four frame sizes (S-XL). But small bikes are only available with 27.5″ rear wheels (no more <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/canyon-torque-freeride-park-bike-sends-gravity-tech-evolved-dh/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">XS</a> size), and extra-large bikes are only available with 29″ front wheels. (<em>S0, 27.5=S-L; Mullet &amp; 29=M-XL</em>).</p><h3>Rampage-proven, Freeride-ready</h3><div id=\"attachment_280112\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103928/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Red-Bull-Rampage-Tommy-G.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-280112\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103928/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Red-Bull-Rampage-Tommy-G.jpg\" alt=\"Tommy G at Red Bull Rampage on the new 2022 Canyon Torque freeride mountain bike\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103928/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Red-Bull-Rampage-Tommy-G.jpg 1500w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103928/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Red-Bull-Rampage-Tommy-G-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103928/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Red-Bull-Rampage-Tommy-G-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103928/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Red-Bull-Rampage-Tommy-G-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103928/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Red-Bull-Rampage-Tommy-G-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-280112\"><em>2021 Red Bull Rampage</em></p></div><p>Whip it, flip it, throw down a 360° or two. While Canyon admits that the newly longer &amp; slacker Torque was built more for bikeparks and fast jump lines than throwing down tricks, it’s certainly capable in that manner too. In fact, the new bike was one of the few we didn’t share from our <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/13-rampage-pro-bikes-mega-custom-freeride-rig-roundup-of-2021-red-bull-rampage/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Red Bull Rampage roundup</a> since it wasn’t yet official.</p><p>But Canyon CLLCTV rider Tommy G put a new blacked-out carbon Torque through the paces at this year’s Rampage, spinning it around &amp; round. Canyon suggests riders looking to “throw shapes” on the new bike should probably stick with the 27.5″ wheeled versions, and likely pick one size smaller bike to ride.</p><p>The new Torque is also rated for the same Category 5 as their DH bikes, and you can even mount a double crown fork. Although again, Canyon recommends reducing DH fork travel back to 180 or 190mm to preserve the new freeride bike’s handling.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103925/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Sam-Soriano-climbing.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103925/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Sam-Soriano-climbing.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Torque freeride bikepark bike, Samantha Soriano climbing\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103925/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Sam-Soriano-climbing.jpg 1800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103925/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Sam-Soriano-climbing-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103925/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Sam-Soriano-climbing-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103925/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Sam-Soriano-climbing-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103925/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Sam-Soriano-climbing-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103925/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_Sam-Soriano-climbing-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"></a></p><p>But while the new&nbsp;Canyon Torque can go big, it is also a much better climber now too with that super steep seat angle. Not every steep descent is lift-served.</p><p>The new Torque isn’t going to rocket up the climbs like an XC bike, Canyon’s four-bar Triple Phase suspension does a solid job climbing. And with lockout levers spec’d on all of the shocks, it’ll simply be a matter of patiently sitting &amp; spinning to get back up for another run.</p><h3>Tech details – What’s new?</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103922/2022-Canyon-Torque-CF7-freeride-bike_carbon-275-angled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103922/2022-Canyon-Torque-CF7-freeride-bike_carbon-275-angled.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Torque carbon freeride bikepark bike, angled\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103922/2022-Canyon-Torque-CF7-freeride-bike_carbon-275-angled.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103922/2022-Canyon-Torque-CF7-freeride-bike_carbon-275-angled-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103922/2022-Canyon-Torque-CF7-freeride-bike_carbon-275-angled-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103922/2022-Canyon-Torque-CF7-freeride-bike_carbon-275-angled-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103922/2022-Canyon-Torque-CF7-freeride-bike_carbon-275-angled-768x576.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103922/2022-Canyon-Torque-CF7-freeride-bike_carbon-275-angled-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>Besides more wheel size options, Canyon says they paired the updated longer &amp; slacker geometry with reduced offset forks to hit a sweet spot of high-speed stability, playfulness, and climb-ability from the new, more versatile long-travel park bike. Both alloy &amp; carbon frames are also stiffer and more durable than before.</p><p>Plus, now there’s room for a bottle cage under the shock for a 600ml side-load cage and a 2-bolt spare tube/tool mount just behind the headtube in the front triangle, as well.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103918/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon-frame-details.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103918/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon-frame-details.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Torque freeride bikepark bike, carbon frame details\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103918/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon-frame-details.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103918/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon-frame-details-297x149.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103918/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon-frame-details-800x400.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103918/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon-frame-details-120x60.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103918/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon-frame-details-768x384.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103918/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon-frame-details-1536x768.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p>The new carbon Torques get flip-chip adjustable geometry, and the option for mullet builds, plus other similar tech like the Spectral. That means&nbsp;integrated downtube protection, chunky integrated chain slap damping chainstay protectors, clever hide-away QR rear thru-axles, BSA threaded bottom brackets, and internal cable routing with full-length guides.</p><p>All of the new Canyon Torque freeride bikes get mini chain guides standard, while the carbon frames can have an additional set of ISCG tabs added later, and the alloy bikes have tabs welded on. Canyon says the new Torque shares many replacement items with the Spectral, like the optional ISCG mounting plate, replaceable thread inserts at all pivots (alloy for carbon frames, steel for alloy bikes), UDH universal derailleur hanger, and sealed bearings with proprietary long-lasting grease fill.</p><div id=\"attachment_280107\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103915/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon-vs-alloy-frame-details.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-280107\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103915/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon-vs-alloy-frame-details.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Torque freeride bikepark bike, carbon vs. alloy frames\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103915/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon-vs-alloy-frame-details.jpg 1800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103915/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon-vs-alloy-frame-details-297x165.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103915/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon-vs-alloy-frame-details-800x444.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103915/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon-vs-alloy-frame-details-120x67.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103915/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon-vs-alloy-frame-details-768x427.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103915/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon-vs-alloy-frame-details-1536x853.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-280107\">carbon vs. alloy</p></div><p>Both new frame options are also said to save over more than two hundred grams over their predecessors.</p><p>The new carbon Canyon Torque frame sheds its weight via updated layup that promises a boosted stiffness-to-weight ratio, plus weight savings from the new full-carbon rear end. Now down to 2652g for the full carbon frameset, it gets the same Category 5 rating as Canyon’s DH World Cup-winning <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/canyon-sender-cfr-gives-carbon-dh-race-mountain-bike-all-new-lighter-faster-update/\">Sender</a>.</p><p>The alloy bike drops 250g over the previous model, while still delivering the same stiffness as the carbon bikes thanks to more careful tube shaping &amp; butting, prioritizing performance over just trying to minim the more swoopy looks of the carbon frames. Stronger, stiffer, AND lighter than the old aluminum version, the new Torque AL frame now comes in at 3250g, just 600g (or one water bottle) heavier than the carbon bike, making it a solid option for riders looking to save some cash to bike lift tickets.</p><h3>2022 Canyon Torque – Pricing, options &amp; availability</h3><p>The all-new 2022 Canyon Torque freeride bike is now available in aluminum or carbon framesets, in 27.5″ or 29″ wheel builds, or even a couple of mullet combo options in carbon only. Final spec and real availability varies a bit from market to market, with six models officially in total, three of which are being offered now in the US.</p><div id=\"attachment_280105\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103908/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_alloy-aluminum_torque-5.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-280105\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103908/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_alloy-aluminum_torque-5.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Torque freeride bikepark bike, alloy Torque 5\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103908/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_alloy-aluminum_torque-5.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103908/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_alloy-aluminum_torque-5-297x178.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103908/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_alloy-aluminum_torque-5-800x480.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103908/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_alloy-aluminum_torque-5-120x72.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103908/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_alloy-aluminum_torque-5-768x461.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103908/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_alloy-aluminum_torque-5-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-280105\">2022 Canyon Torque 5</p></div><p>The Torque gets two alloy models in either 27.5″ or 29er options, starting with the $3300 / 2700€ Torque AL 5 spec’d with Shimano Deore 1×12, a RockShox ZEB Select/Super Deluxe Select+ suspension setup &amp; RaceFace AR30 wheels, at a claimed 16.4kg (36.2lb).</p><p>A second alloy Canyon Torque 6 gets upgraded to SLX, Fox 38/Float X2 Performance suspension, and gravity-ready wheels specifically developed for the Torques with DT Swiss, for 3200€ at 16.1kg.</p><div id=\"attachment_280104\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103904/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon_torque-cf-7.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-280104\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103904/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon_torque-cf-7.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Torque freeride bikepark bike, carbon Torque CF 7\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103904/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon_torque-cf-7.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103904/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon_torque-cf-7-297x178.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103904/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon_torque-cf-7-800x480.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103904/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon_torque-cf-7-120x72.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103904/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon_torque-cf-7-768x461.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103904/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon_torque-cf-7-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-280104\">2022 Canyon Torque CF 7</p></div><p>The carbon bikes start with the 15.5kg (34.2lb) Torque CF 7 for $4400 / 3700€ with SRAM GX Eagle mechanical, RockShox ZEB Select+ &amp; Super Deluxe Select+ suspension, plus the alloy DT Swiss FR2070 wheelset.</p><div id=\"attachment_280103\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103901/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon_torque-cf-8.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-280103\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103901/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon_torque-cf-8.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Torque freeride bikepark bike, carbon Torque 8\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103901/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon_torque-cf-8.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103901/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon_torque-cf-8-297x178.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103901/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon_torque-cf-8-800x480.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103901/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon_torque-cf-8-120x72.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103901/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon_torque-cf-8-768x461.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103901/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_carbon_torque-cf-8-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-280103\">2022 Canyon Torque CF 8 Mullet</p></div><p>Mullet combos are only available in two top carbon spec for the time being <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/review-canyon-spectral-mullet-cf-cllctv-shifts-capable-trail-bike-to-enduro/\">like the Spectral</a> we’ve already tested. Although we have a feeling that Canyon is just testing the mullet waters, and will likely add more options if these sell really well. It seems that it will literally be as easy as sticking together an alloy 27.5 rear triangle to an alloy front triangle. (<em>Individual carbon &amp; alloy frame sections are not interchangeable between different materials.</em>)</p><p>The most affordable mullet bike is the 15.8kg (34.8lb) $5400 / 4500€ Torque CF 8 with Shimano XT, a Fox 38 Performance Elite fork, Fox DHX2 Performance Elite coil shock, and a DT Swiss FR560 wheelset with 350 Ratchet hubs.</p><p>A second, special edition Torque CF Fabio Wibmer bike also gets a mullet wheel setup, plus Öhlins suspension with a RXF38 fork and TTX22M coil shock, plus a mixed SRAM X01/GX Eagle build &amp; the DT FR560 wheels – selling for 5500€ at claimed weight of 15.6kg.</p><p>(<em>Neither Mullet build is available with matched wheel size pairs.</em>)</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103857/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-Bikepark-Schladming-AT.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103857/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-Bikepark-Schladming-AT.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Torque freeride bike, riding bikepark Schladming\" width=\"1500\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103857/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-Bikepark-Schladming-AT.jpg 1500w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103857/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-Bikepark-Schladming-AT-297x178.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103857/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-Bikepark-Schladming-AT-800x480.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103857/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-Bikepark-Schladming-AT-120x72.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/06103857/2022-Canyon-Torque-freeride-mountain-bike_mullet-Bikepark-Schladming-AT-768x461.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\"></a></p><p>On top, there’s also a premium race-ready 5800€ Canyon Torque CF 9 carbon bike build with XTR, Fox 38/Float X2 Factory suspension, and DT FR560 wheels with 240 EXP hubs at just 14.7kg (available in 27.5 or 29″, not mullet.)</p><p>Many of the new carbon Torques are available in stock now in a number of wheelsize, color &amp; spec combos. but it looks like buyers of the aluminum bikes will have to wait a bit longer. US customers look like they will get the entry bike first. But alloy bikes should start showing up on mountain bikers’ doorsteps globally from early to mid-January 2022, with plenty of time to get dialed in before most bikeparks open back up after ski season.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.canyon.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Canyon.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"1d2390620fa31e827d0536d57b1c6a1b6f30edd858a693269d5ace1596858fb9","category":"Cycling"}